#R > residuals. <- function(object, type = "pearson", ...) {
#R +     if (type != "martingale") {
#R +         cl <- match.call()
#R +         cl[[1]] <- quote(stats::residuals)
#R +         return(eval(cl, parent.frame()))
#R +     }
#R +     stopifnot(inherits(object, "glm"), object$family$family == 
#R +         "poisson", object$family$link == "log", all(object$y %in% 
#R +         0:1))
#R +     offs <- object$offset
#R +     etas <- object$linear.predictors - offs
#R +     ys <- object$y
#R +     ys - exp(etas + offs)
#R + }

Create summary statistics table

local({
  frm_vars <- 
    ~ dtd + excess_ret + r_wcapq_atq + r_oiadpq_atq + 
    r_mv_ltq + r_niq_atq + r_ltq_atq + r_actq_lctq + sigma + 
    rel_size + actq_defl_log - 1
  
  mm <- model.matrix(frm_vars, dat)
  vs <- all.vars(frm_vars)
  labs <- sapply(vs, get_label)
  
  ss <- t(apply(mm, 2, function(x){
    qs <- quantile(x, c(.01, .99))
    x <- pmin(pmax(x, qs[1]), qs[2])
    c(mean = mean(x), median = median(x), `standard deviation` = sd(x),  
      `1% quantile` = qs[1], `99% quantile` = qs[2])
  }))
  print(ss) # to check the result
  ss <- structure(sprintf("%.3f", ss), .Dim = dim(ss), .Dimnames = 
                    dimnames(ss))
  
  cat("\\begin{tabular}{lrrrrr}\n",
      "\\toprule",
      "& Mean & Median & Standard deviation & 1\\% & 99\\%",
      "\\\\\n\\midrule\n")
  for(i in 1:nrow(ss))
    cat(labs[i], "&", paste0(ss[i, ], collapse = " & "), "\\\\\n")
  cat("\\bottomrule\n\\end{tabular}")
})

Example in Paper

#####
# assign function to simulate outcome
n_periods <- 64L + 1L

# means for mixture component with time-varying means
mea_min <- -3
mea_max <- 2
mid <- (n_periods - 1L) / 2L 
tfunc <- abs(1:n_periods - mid - 1L)
tfunc <- (tfunc - min(tfunc)) / (max(tfunc) - min(tfunc)) * 
  (mea_max - mea_min) + mea_min
plot(tfunc, type = "l")

# assign simulation function
get_dat <- function(){
  sim_dat <- replicate(1000, {
    # draw starting time
    tstart <- (sample.int(n_periods, 1L) - 1L):(n_periods - 1L)
    
    # draw covariates
    n <- length(tstart)
    X <- ifelse(
      .2 > runif(n), 
      rnorm(n * 1L, mean = tfunc[tstart + 1L], sd = .5), 
      rnorm(n * 1L))
    
    # determine if individual has an event and remove observations after
    # if so
    y <- -expm1(-exp(X - 3)) > runif(n) 
    idx <- if(any(y)) 1:min(which(y)) else 1:n
    
    # return 
    data.frame(X, y = y, tstop = tstart + 1L, tstart = tstart)[idx, ]
  }, simplify = FALSE)
  do.call(rbind, sim_dat)
}

# show example
set.seed(18404064)
tmp <- get_dat()
ggplot(tmp, aes(x = X, y = as.factor(tstop))) + 
  stat_density_ridges(scale = 3, fill = rgb(0, 0, 0, 0), quantile_lines = TRUE, 
                      quantiles = 2) + theme_ridges() +
  scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0.01, 0)) +
  scale_y_discrete(expand = c(0.01, 0)) + labs(y = "tstop")
#R Picking joint bandwidth of 0.347

# simulate

# knot positions
(knt <- seq(1, n_periods, length.out = 5L)[-c(1, 5)])
#R [1] 17 33 49
# simulate and compute
cl <- makeCluster(6L)
set.seed(28789699)
clusterExport(cl, c("knt", "n_periods", "n_periods", "get_dat", "tfunc"), 
              envir = environment())
clusterSetRNGStream(cl)

out <- parLapply(cl, 1:1000L, function(...){
  library(splines)
  
  # simulate data and fit true model
  sim_dat <- get_dat()
  f1 <- glm(y ~ X, binomial("cloglog"), sim_dat)
  
  # aggregate data 
  sim_col <- lapply(split(sim_dat, sim_dat$tstop), function(x){
    n <- nrow(x)
    with(x, data.frame(n = n, y = sum(y) / n, X = mean(X), tstart = tstart[1L], 
                       tstop = tstop[1L]))
  })
  sim_col <- do.call(rbind, sim_col)
  
  # fit models to aggregate data
  f2 <- glm(y ~ X, binomial("cloglog"), sim_col, weights = n)
  
  # add splines
  f3 <- update(f2, . ~ . + ns(tstop, knots = knt))
  
  list(f1 = f1, f2 = f2, f3 = f3)
}, simplify = FALSE)

stopCluster(cl)
#####
# gather result
ests <- local({
  ests <- lapply(out, function(o) sapply(o, function(m) coef(m)))
  out <- lapply(seq_along(ests[[1L]]), function(i) sapply(ests, "[[", i))
  names(out) <- names(ests[[1L]])
  out
})

# MC means and standard errors
(summas <- lapply(ests, function(x) apply(x, 1L, function(z){
  mea <- mean(z)
  sdo <- sd(z) / sqrt(length(z))
  c(mean = mea, sd = sdo)
})))

# likelihood ratio tests
z <- lapply(out, function(x) anova(x$f2, x$f3, test = "LRT"))
ps <- sapply(lapply(z, "[", TRUE, "Pr(>Chi)"), "[[", 2L)
plot(ecdf(ps))
abline(a = 0, b = 1, lty = 2)

sum(ps < 0.05)
